Animating height from `0` to `auto` is a classic CSS challenge. The CSS grid trick provides a pure CSS solution that works with Tailwind.

```css
/* globals.css */
.animate-grid-rows {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-rows: 0fr;
  transition: grid-template-rows 0.3s ease-out;
}

.animate-grid-rows[data-open="true"] {
  grid-template-rows: 1fr;
}

.animate-grid-rows > * {
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

```tsx
import { useState } from 'react';

export function Collapsible({ title, children }: { title: string; children: React.ReactNode }) {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);

  return (
    <div className="border rounded-lg">
      <button
        onClick={() => setOpen(!open)}
        className="w-full px-4 py-3 text-left font-medium flex justify-between items-center"
        aria-expanded={open}
      >
        {title}
        <span className={`transition-transform duration-300 ${open ? 'rotate-180' : ''}`}>▼</span>
      </button>
      <div className="animate-grid-rows" data-open={open}>
        <div>
          <div className="px-4 pb-3">{children}</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

The trick: a grid container with `grid-template-rows: 0fr` collapses its child to zero height. Transitioning to `1fr` smoothly expands to the content's natural height. The child must have `overflow: hidden`. This avoids JavaScript measurement, `requestAnimationFrame`, or `max-height` hacks. Works in all modern browsers.

Tailwind v4 introduces significant changes. Here are the critical differences when migrating from v3.

**Configuration: JS to CSS**
```javascript
// v3 — tailwind.config.js (REMOVED)
module.exports = {
  content: ['./src/**/*.tsx'],
  theme: { extend: { colors: { brand: '#3b82f6' } } },
};
```
```css
/* v4 — app.css */
@import 'tailwindcss';
@theme {
  --color-brand: #3b82f6;
}
```

**Changed utilities:**
```
/* v3 → v4 */
bg-opacity-50 → bg-black/50
text-opacity-75 → text-white/75
ring-offset-2 → ring-2 ring-offset-2 (separate utilities)
decoration-2 → decoration-2 (unchanged)
shadow-sm → shadow-sm (unchanged)
```

**New features:**
```css
/* @starting-style for entry animations */
.card {
  transition: opacity 0.3s;
  @starting-style {
    opacity: 0;
  }
}

/* Container queries built-in */
@utility custom-util {
  /* Define custom utilities in CSS */
}

@custom-variant dark (&:where(.dark, .dark *));
```

**Automatic migration:**
```bash
npx @tailwindcss/upgrade
```

**Key breaking changes:** `@apply` in external CSS files requires `@reference` import. The `screens` config is replaced by `--breakpoint-*` variables. `safelist` is removed — use `@source` instead. PostCSS plugin changes from `tailwindcss` to `@tailwindcss/postcss`. The upgrade tool handles most changes automatically.

Skip navigation links allow keyboard users to bypass repetitive navigation and jump directly to main content. This is a WCAG 2.1 Level A requirement.

```tsx
// components/skip-nav.tsx
export function SkipNav() {
  return (
    <a
      href="#main-content"
      className="sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-[100] focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:bg-white focus:text-black focus:rounded-md focus:shadow-lg focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary"
    >
      Skip to main content
    </a>
  );
}
```

```tsx
// app/layout.tsx
import { SkipNav } from '@/components/skip-nav';

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        <SkipNav />
        <header>...</header>
        <main id="main-content" tabIndex={-1}>
          {children}
        </main>
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

The `sr-only` class hides the link visually but keeps it in the tab order. When focused (Tab key), `focus:not-sr-only` makes it visible. The `tabIndex={-1}` on `<main>` allows it to receive focus programmatically. This pattern is invisible to mouse users but essential for keyboard navigation. Test by pressing Tab immediately after page load.

Tailwind CSS v4 changes the PostCSS plugin and handles nesting internally, so the setup differs from v3.

**Tailwind v4 PostCSS config:**
